A bride and one of her maids were abducted when terrorists stormed a wedding ceremony at Lavun Local Government in Niger on Saturday. It was learnt terrorists disrupted the wedding with guests and hosts taking to their heels. They also destroyed vehicles and other decorations at the ceremony while shooting indiscriminately.   NDLEA intercepts 649, 300 tramadol, 809, 850 Euros     Internet interruptions: Elon Musk activates satellites in…     Stranded Africans lament maltreatment at Poland-Ukraine…   Six persons, including two vigilante members, were among those killed in the process. The terrorists, residents said, divided themselves into three groups after the operation to share rustled cattle. The Commissioner for local government and internal security, Emmanuel Umar, confirmed the incident. He said full details would be made available shortly.